Which property serves as the discriminant in this union?

```ts
type Circle = { kind: 'circle'; radius: number };
type Square = { kind: 'square'; side: number };
type Shape = Circle | Square;
```

How does TypeScript narrow the type inside this switch?

```ts
function area(shape: Shape) {
  switch (shape.kind) {
    case 'circle':
      return Math.PI * shape.radius ** 2;
    case 'square':
      return shape.side ** 2;
  }
}
```

